    <text>
        <body>
            <head>115. Telegram From the Embassy in <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH"
                    >Libya</placeName> to the Department of State<note n="1" place="foot"
                    type="source" xml:id="d115fn1">Source: Carter Library, National Security
                    Affairs, Staff Material, Middle East, Subject File, Box 61, Libya: 1–12/79.
                    Secret; Immediate; <gloss target="#t_Exdis_1">Exdis</gloss>. Printed from a copy
                    that was received in the White House Situation Room.</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Tripoli</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1979-12-14T13:15:00+00:00">December 14, 1979, 1315Z</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>1925. Subject: Basis for a Continuing <rs type="compound-subject"
                    corresp="recRtTKQqtxKMBMhV">Diplomatic Relationship</rs> With <placeName
                    corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName>.</p>
            <p>1. (S–Entire text).</p>
            <p>2. As part of the <orgName corresp="rec7Bg5QUDG0eHqgl">Department</orgName>’s
                documentation on <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName> I submit
                comments by Political Officer Hooper. I cannot take exception to them though there
                are other considerations that should be discussed before final decisions are made.
                The following five premises, tested by our experiences in Tripoli, reflect our
                judgements about the foundations of U.S.-<placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH"
                    >Libyan</placeName> interests:</p>
            <p>—A. <persName corresp="recQAFmups6ngiYAU">Qadhafi</persName> is prone to lie. This
                habit tends to raise doubts about the validity of his remarks contained in official
                exchanges or public utterances, and about reassurances and pledges conveyed by his
                representatives in the <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libyan</placeName>
                Government.</p>
            <p>—B. The U.S.-<placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libyan</placeName>
                <rs type="topic" corresp="recUatc2rZ79DXSzf">petroleum</rs> relationship is
                self-sustaining. Although American <rs type="topic" corresp="recQZssarRbcJz7o2">oil
                    company</rs> officials find a U.S. diplomatic presence convenient, the absence
                of U.S. diplomats from Tripoli would not have a significant impact on economic
                relations predicated upon a clear mutuality of interests.</p>
            <p>—C. U.S.-<placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libyan</placeName>
                educational/cultural ties are also to some extent self-sustaining. <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="receqDO15mlMSmrzP">Visa</rs> services for <placeName
                    corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libyan</placeName> students can be provided by other
                U.S. Embassies in <placeName corresp="recp8rWUqC6nWf8T5">Europe</placeName> and the
                    <placeName corresp="recJAi0OpNdSuYev5">Middle East</placeName>.</p>
            <p>—D. The U.S.-<placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libyan</placeName> political
                dialogue will flounder as long as <persName corresp="recQAFmups6ngiYAU"
                    >Qadhafi</persName> remains in power. The <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH"
                    >Libyan</placeName> leader is fundamentally opposed to U.S. political interests
                in the <placeName corresp="recJAi0OpNdSuYev5">Middle East</placeName>.</p>
            <p>—E. A U.S. diplomatic presence of undetermined size can provide useful information
                about developments in <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName> to
                the Washington community. The utility of such a presence, however, must be carefully
                assessed in the context of the above premises.</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>
                    <persName corresp="recHqwjnAq6PNvMcs">
                        <hi rendition="simple_bold">Eagleton</hi>
                    </persName>
                </signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
